@iSazonov There is also a `StringUtil` class in `System.Management.Automation.SecurityAccountsManager` and `Microsoft.PowerShell.ScheduledJob`. Maybe we can remove duplicated code if we make the class `public`?

Also, the `Format` method in `Microsoft.PowerShell.ScheduledJob` uses `Threading.Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentCulture` as the `IFormatProvider` which I'm not sure is correct (see https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.threading.thread.currentculture?view=net-5.0#remarks)

<blockquote><img src="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/media/logos/logo-ms-social.png" width="48" align="right"><div><strong><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.threading.thread.currentculture">Thread.CurrentCulture Property (System.Threading)</a></strong></div><div>Gets or sets the culture for the current thread. </div></blockquote>
